# .env.example
#
# WHAT THIS FILE IS: a TEMPLATE showing which secret values JARVIS needs.
# It contains NO real secrets and IS safe to commit to git.
#
# HOW TO USE IT:
#   1. Copy this file and rename the copy to exactly ".env" (no extension)
#   2. Replace the placeholders below with your real keys
#   3. Never share your real .env file or commit it to git — it's already
#      listed in .gitignore, so a normal `git add .` will skip it safely.
#   4. If you ever paste a real key/token into a chat, terminal share, or
#      screenshot, treat it as compromised and regenerate it immediately.

# REQUIRED — get a FREE key (no credit card required):
#   https://aistudio.google.com/apikey  -> Sign in -> Create API key
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-api-key-goes-here

# OPTIONAL — only needed for GitHub features (checking issues/PRs on
# PRIVATE repos, or creating a new issue). Reading PUBLIC repos' issues
# and PRs works without this, just rate-limited more strictly by GitHub.
# Create a token (classic, "repo" scope is enough) at:
#   https://github.com/settings/tokens
GITHUB_TOKEN=your-github-token-goes-here
